AN ACT relating to manufactured housing; revising provisions
governing the issuance of a new certificate of title by the
Housing Division of the Department of Business and
Industry for a manufactured home, mobile home or
commercial coach when the previously issued certificate
of title is unavailable; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law sets forth various requirements and restrictions relating to the
2 issuance of a certificate of title by the Housing Division of the Department of
3 Business and Industry for a manufactured home, mobile home, manufactured
4 building or commercial coach or factory-built housing. (NRS 489.501-489.585)
5 Under existing law, if a person who is applying for the issuance of a certificate of
6 ownership for a manufactured home, mobile home or commercial coach from the
7 Division is unable to present the previously issued certificate of title because it is
8 unavailable, the Division is authorized to: (1) receive the application, examine the
9 circumstances of the case and require the filing of affidavits or other information;
10 and (2) issue a new certificate of title to the applicant when the Division is satisfied
11 that the applicant is entitled to the certificate. (NRS 489.561) Existing law: (1)
12 provides an additional procedure for obtaining a certificate of title if the applicant is
13 unable to provide satisfactory information to the Division that the applicant is
14 entitled to the certificate, which involves the provision of a bond by the applicant
15 and an inspection by the Division; and (2) requires the Administrator of the
16 Division to adopt regulations regarding this procedure. (NRS 489.562, 489.585)
17 Sections 2 and 3 of this bill require, under either procedure, the Division to either
18 issue a new certificate of title to an applicant or deny the application within 45 days
19 after the date on which the requirements for applying for a certificate of title have
20 been completed. Sections 2 and 3 require the Division to provide an applicant with
21 written notification of and the reasons for the denial of the application. Section 4 of
22 this bill requires the Administrator to adopt regulations to establish an expedited
